---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Downloadable datasets (files live in public/data).
const downloads: { title: string; desc: string; format: string; href: string }[] = [
  {
    title: 'South Street Fieldwork Data',
    desc: 'Parcel- and block-level field-survey data, with condition, vacancy, tenant, and OPA-enrichment fields.',
    format: 'XLSX',
    href: '/data/south-street-fieldwork-data.xlsx',
  },
  {
    title: 'Corridor demographics, 1970 to 2020',
    desc: 'Population, age, income, and housing for the neighborhoods around both corridors, with a data dictionary and methodology.',
    format: 'XLSX',
    href: '/data/corridor-demographics-1970-2020.xlsx',
  },
  {
    title: 'Vacancy and vibrancy analysis',
    desc: 'The cyclical corridor-health curve and vacancy bellwether, with full sources.',
    format: 'XLSX',
    href: '/data/south-street-vacancy-vibrancy-analysis.xlsx',
  },
  {
    title: 'Critical mass summary',
    desc: 'The catchment population and density behind the 276 vs 400 benchmark.',
    format: 'CSV',
    href: '/data/corridor-critical-mass-summary.csv',
  },
  {
    title: 'Building-level parcel data',
    desc: 'The flat, analysis-ready parcel dataset, owner names removed.',
    format: 'CSV',
    href: '/data/building-level-parcel-data.csv',
  },
];
---

<Layout title="About · Saving South Street">
  <div class="finding-wrap">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section>
      <p class="finding-kicker">About</p>
      <h1 class="finding-hero-title">About This Project</h1>
      <p class="finding-byline">An urban planning thesis by Brandon K. Engelhardt | 2026</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
        <a
          href="/thesis.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-stone-500 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-stone-800"
        >Read the full thesis (PDF)</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW THE STUDY WAS DONE -->
    <section class="finding-section">
      <p class="finding-kicker">Methods</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">How the study was done</h2>
      <div class="finding-statblock">
        <div class="finding-stat-items">
          <div class="finding-stat-item">
            <span class="finding-stat-num">519</span>
            <span class="finding-stat-label">parcels walked across both corridors</span>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-stat-item">
            <span class="finding-stat-num">17</span>
            <span class="finding-stat-label">stakeholder interviews</span>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-stat-item">
            <span class="finding-stat-num">30+</span>
            <span class="finding-stat-label">fields coded per parcel</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="finding-body">
        The Philadelphia City Planning Commission set the precedent for this kind of fieldwork with its
        Philadelphia Shops surveys in 1989, 1996, and 2004, walking the city's commercial corridors
        with clipboards and pencils. This study did the same forty years later, with an iPad and a
        pointer finger, because no municipal system captures parcel-level business tenancy at the
        granularity this analysis needed.
      </p>
      <p class="finding-body">
        Fieldwork covered 519 parcels across both corridors in March and April 2026. South Street's
        271 parcels were walked five times, on weekday mornings, Friday afternoons, and a Saturday
        midday; East Passyunk's were walked three times. Each parcel was pre-loaded from Philadelphia's
        Atlas tool, triangulated with OpenDataPhilly and Google Maps, and coded on the spot across
        roughly 30 fields. The four anchor variables were vacancy status, structural condition,
        storefront condition, and business category, with separate trips dedicated to block-level
        streetscape, walking conditions, and quality of life.
      </p>
      <p class="finding-body">
        The field survey was joined to public records to build the full picture: Office of Property
        Assessment data on sales, values, and year built; License and Inspections violation history;
        Census and American Community Survey demographics back to 1970; and the PCPC Philadelphia Shops
        inventories for the historical vacancy baseline. Each variable's definition lives in the source
        line of the figure or table where it appears.
      </p>
      <p class="finding-body">
        Fieldwork was paired with 17 scheduled interviews across six categories of corridor actor:
        business-district leaders, civic-association presidents, two City Council offices, the
        Department of Commerce, business owners, and a retail brokerage. Interviews ran 30 to 60
        minutes, in person, over Zoom, and by phone. Each transcript was coded into themes, with AI
        assistance, and shared back with the interviewee for confirmation. Recurring concerns, absentee
        landlords, smoke shops, and low housing density, shaped the diagnosis. To protect the people
        who spoke candidly, this site refers to them by role rather than by name.
      </p>
      <p class="finding-body">
        A few limitations are worth naming. The study leans toward South Street, with less depth on
        East Passyunk and on the corridor's pre-1960s history. The four proposals are vision-based
        recommendations, not financial models, and each still needs a dedicated return-on-investment
        analysis. The study also had no direct visitation data, such as Placer.ai mobility data, so
        demand was triangulated from tenant mix, field survey, and interviews rather than measured
        directly. As a single-researcher project by someone who lives within the corridor's catchment,
        it carries a resident's perspective, which opened doors but also brings its own framing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ABOUT THE AUTHOR -->
    <section class="finding-section">
      <p class="finding-kicker">About the author</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">About the author</h2>
      <div class="about-author">
        <img
          class="about-author-photo"
          src="/images/brandon.jpg"
          alt="Brandon Engelhardt, the author of this study."
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
        <div class="about-author-body">
          <p class="finding-body about-author-text">
            Brandon Engelhardt is the author of this study and a Master of Regional and City Planning
            graduate of Drexel University. A Pottstown, Pennsylvania native and University of
            Pennsylvania graduate, he spent more than a decade in technology, including over seven
            years working with public sector clients. His planning work focuses on pro-growth public
            policy that strengthens Philadelphia's business competitiveness, supports new business
            creation, expands higher-wage opportunities, and improves the city's work/live/play
            balance. Brandon serves on the board of the Society Hill Civic Association, runs Join, or
            Die! Tours through Society Hill and Old City, and is an Irish Setter aficionado.
          </p>
          <p class="about-author-link-row">
            <a
              class="about-inline-link"
              href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/brandonengelhardt"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
            >Connect on LinkedIn</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DATA AND DOWNLOADS -->
    <section class="finding-section">
      <p class="finding-kicker">Data</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">Data and downloads</h2>
      <p class="finding-body">
        The data behind this study is open to download and reuse. Interviewee contact information has
        been removed to protect the people who spoke for it.
      </p>
      <ul class="about-downloads">
        {downloads.map((d) => (
          <li class="about-download">
            <span class="about-download-info">
              <span class="about-download-title">{d.title}</span>
              <span class="about-download-desc">{d.desc}</span>
            </span>
            <a class="about-download-link" href={d.href} download>Download {d.format}</a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- A NOTE ON AI -->
    <section class="finding-argument" aria-label="A note on AI">
      <p class="finding-argument-kicker">A note on AI</p>
      <p class="finding-argument-text">
        This website is a condensed, interactive companion to the thesis, not a replacement for it. AI
        tools helped summarize the thesis, adapt it into these web pages, and build the interactive
        features. Across many iterations, the work was steered to preserve the author's own words,
        voice, and argument, and every page was reviewed and edited by hand. The complete, fully human
        work, with the full analysis, methods, and citations, is the thesis itself.
      </p>
      <a class="analysis-maplink" href="/thesis.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Download the full thesis (PDF)
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- ACKNOWLEDGMENTS -->
    <section class="finding-section">
      <p class="finding-kicker">Acknowledgments</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">Acknowledgments</h2>
      <p class="finding-body">
        Thanks to my thesis advisors at Drexel, and to the corridor stakeholders who gave their time
        and candor in interviews. Their insight shaped both the diagnosis and the proposals.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW TO CITE -->
    <section class="finding-section">
      <p class="finding-kicker">How to cite</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">How to cite</h2>
      <p class="about-citation">
        Engelhardt, Brandon K. "Saving South Street." Master's thesis, Drexel University, 2026.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CLOSING -->
    <p class="about-updated">Last updated June 2026.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* One unified width, mirroring the Findings and Policy Analysis pages. */
  .finding-wrap {
    max-width: 56rem; /* 896px, narrower than the main's 1104px box so it binds */
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* Hero: a small muted kicker over a large dominant title. */
  .finding-hero-title {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
  }
  .finding-thesis {
    margin: 0.7rem 0 0;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #44403c; /* stone-700 */
  }
  .finding-byline {
    margin: 0.55rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #78716c; /* stone-500 */
  }

  /* Section rhythm: a thin rule sets each section apart. */
  .finding-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e7e5e4; /* stone-200 */
  }

  .finding-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #78716c; /* stone-500 */
  }

  .finding-body {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    color: #44403c; /* stone-700 */
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Big-number stat block (black and bold). */
  .finding-statblock {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
  }
  .finding-stat-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem 3rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .finding-stat-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .finding-stat-num {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 6vw, 2.75rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900, black */
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .finding-stat-label {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    max-width: 24ch;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #78716c; /* stone-500 */
  }

  /* Callout panel (A note on AI), matching the argument panel on the other pages. */
  .finding-argument {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    background: #f5f5f4; /* stone-100 */
    border-left: 4px solid #1c1917; /* stone-900 accent */
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .finding-argument-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #78716c; /* stone-500 */
  }
  .finding-argument-text {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #292524; /* stone-800 */
  }

  /* Prominent black download button (same treatment as the density button). */
  .analysis-maplink {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.3rem;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: #1c1917; /* stone-900, black */
    color: #fafaf9; /* stone-50 */
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
    transition:
      background-color 0.12s ease,
      box-shadow 0.12s ease;
  }
  .analysis-maplink:hover {
    background: #292524; /* stone-800 */
    box-shadow: 0 5px 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }
  .analysis-maplink:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #1c1917;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* Author block: a small rounded headshot beside the text. */
  .about-author {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .about-author-photo {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 1px solid #e7e5e4; /* stone-200 */
  }
  .about-author-body {
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .about-author-text {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .about-author-link-row {
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-author {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  .about-inline-link {
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .about-inline-link:hover {
    color: #57534e; /* stone-600 */
  }

  /* Downloads list */
  .about-downloads {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .about-download {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid #e7e5e4; /* stone-200 */
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #fafaf9; /* stone-50 */
  }
  .about-download-info {
    display: block;
    flex: 1 1 22rem;
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .about-download-title {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
  }
  .about-download-desc {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: #57534e; /* stone-600 */
  }
  .about-download-link {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.95rem;
    border: 1px solid #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
    text-decoration: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition:
      background-color 0.12s ease,
      color 0.12s ease;
  }
  .about-download-link:hover {
    background: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
    color: #fafaf9; /* stone-50 */
  }
  .about-download-link:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #1c1917;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* Citation block */
  .about-citation {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #f5f5f4; /* stone-100 */
    border: 1px solid #e7e5e4; /* stone-200 */
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #1c1917; /* stone-900 */
  }

  /* Last-updated line */
  .about-updated {
    margin: 3rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e7e5e4; /* stone-200 */
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #a8a29e; /* stone-400 */
  }
</style>
